juan vilariño  malla vial del atlántico consortium  zoominfocom juan vilariño  malla vial del atlántico consortium  zoominfocom idea vilariño  wikipedia idea vilariño from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search idea vilariño a young idea vilariño born august   montevideo died april   aged  montevideo nationality uruguayan occupation writer poet essayist professor translator literary critic movement generación del  idea vilariño montevideo  august  –  april  was a uruguayan poet essayist and literary critic she belonged to the group of intellectuals known as generación del  in this generation there are several writers such as juan carlos onetti mario benedetti sarandy cabrera carlos martínez moreno ángel rama carlos real de azúa carlos maggi alfredo gravina mario arregui amanda berenguer humberto megget emir rodríguez monegal gladys castelvecchi and josé pedro díaz among others she also worked as a translator composer and lecturer contents  biography  works  poetry  essays  translations  references  bibliography  external links biographyedit she was born in an educated middle class family in that time music and literature were always present her father leandro vilariño  was a poet whose works were not edited in his lifetime just like her siblings numen poema azul and alma she studied music her mother was very well educated in european literaturecitation needed as an educator in exercise she was a professor of literature and secondary education since  until the coup of  after the restoration of the democratic system she was a professor in the department of uruguayan and latinamerican literature in the college of education of humanities and sciences of the university of the republic she wrote since she was very young and her first mature poems were designed between  and  years old her first poetic work la suplicante was edited in  with only her name in the subsequent years she would become recognized internationally and awarded with various awards her poems were marked by an intimate experience intense and distressing but always very coherent she integrated the generation of writers diverse nature that arose artistically from  to  that were called the generación del  among the generación del  the following authors can be found juan carlos onetti mario benedetti sarandy cabrera carlos martínez moreno ángel rama carlos real de azúa carlos maggi alfredo gravina mario arregui amanda berenguer humberto megget emir rodríguez monegal gladys castelvecchi josé pedro díaz and others la generación del  for the occasion of the visit of juan ramón jiménez from left to right maría zulema silva vila manuel arturo claps carlos maggi maría inés silva vila juan ramón jiménez idea vilariño emir rodríguez monegal ángel rama sitting josé pedro díaz amanda berenguer zenobia camprubí ida vitale elda lago and manuel flores mora she participated in numerous literary ventures she was one of the founders of the journals clinamen es and número es between  where she met juan ramón jiménez and she was a collaborators to other publications such as marcha la opinión brecha asir and texto crítico idea vilariño at her desk in  her translations also have been the object of recognition with some such as the more recognized works of shakespeare being performed in the theaters of montevideo in  she was interviewed by rosario peyrou and pablo rocca es from where the documentary idea arose the documentary was directed by mario jacob and premiered in may  her work has been translated to various languages like italian german and portuguese as a composer four emblematic songs can be mentioned that are pertinent to popular uruguayan music a una paloma played by daniel viglietti la canción y el poema played by alfredo zitarrosa los orientales and ya me voy pa la guerrilla played by los olimareños in  she received the premio konex konex prize mercosur a las letras granted by the konex foundation argentina as the most influential writer of the region later she had to undergo a surgery that gave her an intestinal and arterial occlusion she did not recover and died in montevideo on  april  worksedit poetryedit la suplicante  cielo cielo  paraíso perdido número  por aire sucio número  nocturnos  poemas de amor  pobre mundo  poesía  no  canciones  poesía     poesía completa montevideo cal y canto  essaysedit grupos simétricos en la poesía de antonio machado  la rima en herrera y reissig  grupos simétricos en poesía  las letras de tango  el tango cantado  translationsedit raymond queneau el rapto de ícaro buenos aires losada  jacques c alexis romancero de las estrellas montevideo arca  william shakespeare hamlet príncipe de dinamarca montevideo ediciones de la banda oriental  andrew cecil bradley macbeth la atmósfera las brujas montevideo editorial técnica  william shakespeare macbeth montevideo editorial técnica  guillermo enrique hudson la tierra purpúrea caracas biblioteca ayacucho  traducida junto con jaime rest guillermo enrique hudson allá lejos y hace tiempo caracas biblioteca ayacucho  traducida junto con jaime rest christine laurent transatlántico adaptación de andré tachiné y philippe arnaud traducción del francés de idea vilariño montevideo trilce  referencesedit  uruguayan poet idea vilariño dies el país  april    idea vilariño wikipedia la enciclopedia libre in spanish    poemas de idea vilariño wwwpoemaspoetascom retrieved    fernando casales idea vilariño eros y tanathos  nº  espéculo ucm pendientedemigracionucmes retrieved    factory troop software fundación konex retrieved   bibliographyedit idea la vida escrita libro álbum contiene entrevistas fragmentos de su diario íntimo y cartas montevideo cal y canto y academia nacional de letras  isbn  external linksedit media related to idea vilariño at wikimedia commons biography of idea vilariño in spanish a media voz in spanish idea antes de idea brecha   check date values in date help in spanish authority control worldcat identities viaf  lccn n isni     gnd  s